The paper discusses the use of data mining techniques for detecting financial accounting fraud, specifically in the insurance sector. This falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) as fraud detection is a crucial aspect of cybersecurity. The use of data mining techniques also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) in the analysis. Dealing with large volumes of financial data requires efficient data processing and management, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of search algorithms for fraud detection, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
